{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0220"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Logging"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0220"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :forestry/logging
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :local-economy :sustainable-forestry]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :logging-coordination-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "LoggingAdvisor ⊣ Logging Coordination Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A verified from-scratch redo
 (see docs/adr/0001-architecture.md) superseding a prior REVERTED
 attempt that shipped with no `deps.edn` and no `registry.cljc`. Four
 ops (`:log-harvest-record` / `:schedule-field-operation` / `:flag-
 safety-concern` / `:order-supplies`), all `:effect :propose` only.
 Nine concrete governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD
 invariants: propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed
 proposal-effect allowlist (no direct felling/skidding-equipment
 control), permanent harvest-cut-plan-finalize block, independent
 site/permit verification, independent permit-allowance recompute for
 felling volume, double-schedule guard, species validation, and
 supply-order total recompute. Safety-concern flagging and over-
 threshold supply orders always escalate to a human logging manager;
 `:log-harvest-record` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
